body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our customer service. My name is Kenneth Washington and I represent SafeRide Car Dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Abigail Martinez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Abigail. To assist you better, may I kindly ask for your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Certainly, it's three four seven - five five five - one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. And could you please provide your email address as well?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is abigail.martinez@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Abigail Martinez, for sharing your information. We'll address your security concerns with utmost priority.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: If you have any further questions or need assistance, feel free to reach out. Thank you for your time.
